.Negotiate exclusive benefits and perks for Loyalty Club members.Expand third-party integrations, ensuring the program generates revenue from multiple sources.6. Marketing &amp; CommunicationCollaborate with the marketing team to run acquisition and retention campaigns.Leverage email marketing, social media, and targeted ads to drive membership growth.Design customer communication strategies that clearly outline the value of the program.7. Technology &amp; Platform ManagementOversee the development of a scalable, user-friendly digital platform for the Loyalty Club.Ensure seamless integration with Alps2Alps services and third-party businesses.Implement real-time analytics to track engagement, revenue, and program performance.Key Success MetricsSubscription Growth Rate – Rapidly scale membership, leveraging the 40,000 existing members.Customer Retention Rate – Maintain high engagement and minimize churn.Cross-Sales Impact – Increase partner revenue through loyalty-driven referrals.Revenue Milestones – Achieve profitability within two years.Qualifications &amp; SkillsProven experience in business development, loyalty programs, or subscription-based business model.Strong understanding of partnership management and revenue-sharing models.Experience in ski tourism, travel, or hospitality industries is a plus.Excellent analytical and financial planning skills.Expertise in digital marketing, customer engagement, and retention strategies.Ability to negotiate high-value contracts with external partners.Strong leadership skills with the ability to scale a business unit from the ground up.Compensation &amp; BenefitsThe Business Owner of Alps2Alps Loyalty Club will receive a highly competitive compensation package, including:Fixed Salary – Providing financial stability while focusing on long-term business growth.Revenue Share Bonus – A performance-based incentive tied to the profitability and revenue growth of the Loyalty Club.Additional Incentives – Bonuses based on key metrics